# Day 01

## Topic

How Computers Work

## What I Learned

- Computer accepts input.
- CPU executes instructions.
- RAM is temporary memory.
- SSD is permanent storage.
- Programs are loaded from SSD to RAM.
- CPU executes instructions from RAM.

## Important Points

- CPU executes instructions.
- RAM is volatile.
- SSD is non-volatile.

## Summary

Today I learned how a computer processes information and the role of CPU, RAM, and SSD.
